Andrew teaches others how to make the shift from fitting meditation in to what you do to bringing meditation in to what you do even if you have many responsibilities. Andrew devoted himself to learn the practice for the first 7 years and then integrated his practice while earning an MBA from the Wharton School and pursuing a career as a Financial Advisor, while also getting married and having 3 children.  

Andrew helps busy professionals go from burnout to balance.

This includes :
Becoming better at listening, parenting and disciplining kids

For Alexandra yoga started out as a last resort. Throughout her childhood, she was a competitive show jumper, spending hours riding horses. Then she abruptly developed chronic fatigue. She struggled with her desire to remain active and healthy when her body was giving out. Yoga became a refuge from the stress and uncertainty in her life. Eventually the cause of her extreme fatigue was treated, however yoga had become an integral part of her life. Once recovered, she jumped back into an active life and found she had a passion for teaching. During this time she continued to practise and became fascinated with the physical aspect of yoga and the role it played in her recovery. In her quest to learn more she began a study of yoga and then meditation.
